                "actions": {
                    "value": ""
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>If a creature is slain by an attack from the soul chain and the forge-spurned is able to retain the creature's corpse, it can bind the creature's soul into the soul chain (as bind soul) with a day of work at a forge and a successful <span data-pf2-check=\"crafting\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-traits=\"divine,fire,necromancy\" data-pf2-label=\"Soul Chain DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Crafting</span> check. An individual whose soul is bound in this way can't be resurrected unless the soul chain is destroyed (Hardness 5, HP 20, BT 10).</p>"
